How did that go?

287
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:56,920
It didn't change anything.

288
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,880
What needed changing?

289
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:03,000
I'd like to be more in control.

290
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:04,720
Why?

291
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:07,600
So people can quit
worrying about me.

292
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,840
Well. I'll tell you something.

293
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:13,880
I'll be straight with you. Okay?

294
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:16,680
I'm not big on control.

295
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,560
But it's your money.

296
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,520
So to speak.

297
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:25,000
So to speak.

298
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,280
Okay.

299
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,400
How's Tuesdays...

300
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,400
and Fridays. Same time?

301
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:39,640
Twice a week?

302
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:42,640
Well. Control's a tough nut.

303
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,480
I've got swim practice every night.

304
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,920
Well. That's a problem.

305
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:52,360
How do we solve that?

306
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:56,120
Guess I'll skip practice
twice a week.

307
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,640
Well. It's up to you.

308
00:19:57,720 --> 00:20:00,160
I don't like being here.

309
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,680
I don't like it at all.

310
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:05,920
Mm-hmm.

311
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:12,600
I saw Mort Swain.
His sister died.

312
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,960
The one from Idaho?

313
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:17,560
The one with the restaurant.

314
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:19,640
She died in Idaho?

315
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,160
I guess so.

316
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,560
Why?

317
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:26,800
You said she was always traveling.

318
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:28,320
I don't know.

319
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:30,160
Maybe in Idaho.

320
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,520
Maybe Kansas City.

321
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,440
I went to see Dr. Berger.

322
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:43,440
Berger?

323
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,200
Yeah.

324
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,920
You didn't say anything. Good!

325
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,600
I went today.

326
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:51,600
I didn't know
you made an appointment.

327
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,920
How was it?

328
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,680
It's a lot of money.

329
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,680
It's okay.

330
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:59,920
It's $50 an hour.
Twice a week.

331
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,960
It's okay.
It is necessary.

332
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,760
What did you talk about?

333
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,040
Not much.

334
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,560
What about your schedule?

335
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:12,280
Well. It'll cut
into swim practice.

336
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:14,440
Where's his office?

337
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:15,960
Highland Park.

338
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,880
Head straight!

339
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:25,400
I don't want to tell you again.

340
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:29,720
This is what I see.

341
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:33,080
I see you yawning
and you coming late.

342
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:35,880
I don't see you having fun.

343
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:38,760
Are you getting enough sleep?

344
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,200
Yeah.

345
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:43,240
Are you having fun?

346
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:44,600
Fun?

347
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:48,200
There's no point
if you're not having fun.

348
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,200
Yeah. I guess so.

349
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,640
You guess so.

350
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,200
Are you on medication?

351
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:57,680
Tranquilizers?

352
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,000
Anything?

353
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:01,600
No. No. Sir.

354
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:04,280
Did I ask you
if they gave you shock?

355
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:05,840
Yeah.

356
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,440
Yeah what?

357
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,320
Yeah. You asked me.

358
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,840
Yeah. They did.

359
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:15,000
Don't look at us. Lazenby.

360
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:17,000
Get in the water!

361
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:25,240
I'm no doctor. Jarrett.

362
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:29,040
I wouldn't let them
put electricity in my head.

363
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:33,080
He drives me nuts!

364
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:35,840
Everybody drives you nuts.

365
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:40,080
Don and Fenetch looked good.

366
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,000
They looked very good.

367
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:45,000
Is he giving you a hard time?

368
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:47,000
Want a clarinet?

369
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:49,000
Van Buren wants a clarinet.

370
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,520
Who's selling it?

371
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,520
My brother.
He needs a motorcycle.

372
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:55,040
You stand behind me
in the choir.

373
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:57,720
Oh. I do?
Is that you?

374
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:00,160
You have a lot of energy.

375
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,240
I do?

376
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:03,040
I mean. That's good.

377
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:05,080
My name's Jeannine Pratt.

378
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:06,560
Nice. Hi.

379
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,080
You're Conrad Jarrett.

380
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,280
Right.

381
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,080
Yeah. Um. Bye.

382
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:14,560
Bye-bye.

383
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:18,560
"You've got a lot of energy."

384
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,560
[Children]
Trick or treat!

385
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:27,080
You're the scariest
ghost I've ever seen!

386
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,600
You look wonderful.

387
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,600
Thank you.

388
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:31,600
There you go.

389
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:33,080
Be careful.

390
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,080
Thank you.
Good-bye.

391
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:38,600
The Cabots.
Julie's first time.

392
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,600
She's so cute!

393
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:45,000
Ha! Ha! Ha! Ha!

394
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:48,280
Know what I've been thinking?

395
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,280
That Christmas in London...

396
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:53,800
would be like something
out of Dickens.

397
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:56,280
We've never done that before.

398
00:23:56,360 --> 00:24:00,800
Maybe we shouldn't plan
to go away right now.

399
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:02,800
We talked about it.

400
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,800
We decided on that.

401
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:06,800
Yeah. I know that.

402
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:09,800
But the timing
doesn't seem right.

403
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,800
We've always gone away
at Christmas.

404
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:15,520
It'd be good for him. Too.

405
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:18,040
Let's get back to normal.

406
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:20,800
He's just started
with this doctor.

407
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,800
He'll miss three weeks.

408
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,320
Why interrupt it?

409
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:27,320
Because I want to get away.

410
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:30,320
I think we should.
It's important.

411
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:34,840
Not if he doesn't
go through with this now.

412
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,320
He might change his mind.

413
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,840
If he changes his mind...

414
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:42,080
it wasn't right for him.

415
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:44,440
Does he want to go?

416
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:47,440
He doesn't know what he wants.

417
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:56,400
Ahh!

418
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:58,160
Don't do that!

419
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:59,680
I'm sorry.

420
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:02,680
I didn't think you were here.

421
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,680
I just got in.

422
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,680
No golf today.
Too cold.

423
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:08,160
How was golf?

424
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:09,680
I didn't play.

425
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:11,160
It's colder today.

426
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:14,680
I mean. For the year.
It's colder.

427
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:17,320
Weren't you swimming?

428
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:19,800
Yeah. Sorry I scared you.

429
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,320
How'd it go?

430
00:27:21,400 --> 00:27:23,320
Good. I swam well.

431
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:24,320
Good.

432
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:27,840
I could swim the 50 if my...

433
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:29,840
my timing got better.

434
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,840
I'm a little off.

435
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:34,320
You must work at that.

436
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:35,320
Yeah.

437
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:39,440
I got 74 on a Trig quiz.

438
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:40,960
74?

439
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:43,960
Gee. I was awful at Trig.

440
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,480
Oh. Yeah? Did you...

441
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:47,720
You took Trig?

442
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,640
Wait a minute.

443
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:55,600
Did I take Trig?

444
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:02,960
I bought you two shirts.
They're on your bed.

445
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:08,560
Who'll be there?

446
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:12,680
Well. The Murrays.
The Gunthers. And the Caines.

447
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:15,520
Let's go to the movies instead.

448
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:18,280
Don't be negative.

449
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:20,680
That's not negative.
That's unpredictable.

450
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:23,080
Let's go to the movies.

451
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,560
Okay.

452
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,160
Really?

453
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:29,000
Okay. Yeah.
Come on. Let's go.

454
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:30,520
What's our excuse?

455
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:35,360
Beth wanted to go
to the movies.

456
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,520
Good.

457
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,120
Very good.

458
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:45,640
All right now. Smile.

459
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:48,560
Remember. Not too many martinis.

460
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:56,640
Will you put that
with the others?

461
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,640
Look. We're in time.

462
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:00,160
Look who's here!

463
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:04,160
Three blocks away
and the last to arrive.

464
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,640
Come on in.

465
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:08,160
Happy birthday!
You look wonderful.

466
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:09,680
Is that new?

467
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,680
Yes. It is.
Do you like it?

468
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:15,080
You did the mousse?

469
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:16,480
It turned out well?

470
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:19,080
Hey. Partner.
How are you?

471
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,840
Hi there.

472
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,800
Hi. Beth.

473
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,400
Good to see you.

474
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:25,800
Borrow the money.

475
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:27,320
I'll go public.

476
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:31,480
I wouldn't do it now
because the market's low.

477
00:29:31,560 --> 00:29:33,320
Your hair looks wonderful.

478
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:35,920
It's shorter. You like it?

479
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:39,600
I said.
"Please put out your cigar."

480
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:43,480
He says. "Huh?
I don't have another one."

481
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:47,080
Good to see you!

482
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,440
You look beautiful. As ever.

483
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:50,920
In school...

484
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:56,120
they think they've got
to walk on the edge of danger.

485
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:58,280
What are these hushed tones?

486
00:29:58,360 --> 00:30:00,400
He told the funniest joke!

487
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,080
I'm not talking to you.

488
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,440
Why?

489
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:10,200
I have my fingers crossed
on this merger.

490
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:11,440
Let's have lunch.

491
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:13,800
I don't know my schedule.

492
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:16,120
I'm free most days.

493
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:18,800
Bob McLean's leaving
Coles and Johnson.

494
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,800
Where is he going?

495
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,840
He doesn't know.

496
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,120
Jesus.

497
00:30:24,200 --> 00:30:25,680
No. You didn't.

498
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:29,080
Isn't he the meanest man
you've met?

499
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,440
When a ball is in play.

500
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:35,480
If a player or caddy
accidentally move it...

501
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:37,680
#Jolly good fellow #

502
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:40,200
# For he's a jolly good fellow ##

503
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:45,480
# Won't regret. Can't forget #

504
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,880
# What we did #

505
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:50,480
# For #

506
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:55,320
# Love ##

507
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,160
Hi. Annie. What's your boy up to?

508
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:03,680
Oh. Who knows?

509
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,520
How's Conrad doing?

510
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:07,520
He's great. Just great.

511
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:11,800
I asked Donald.
He says they haven't talked much.

512
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:14,520
I said maybe he's self-conscious.

513
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:15,520
Oh!

514
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:21,520
No. No. No.

515
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:23,520
No. He's...

516
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:27,120
There's a doctor
in Highland Park...

517
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:29,520
that he sees twice a week.

518
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,880
He's great. Just great.

519
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:35,120
Is he still having some problems?

520
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:37,040
No. Nothing like that.

521
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:39,560
Just somebody to talk to...

522
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:41,960
to polish off the rough edges.

523
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,600
How are you. Darling?

524
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:46,120
Is he falling asleep on you?

525
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:47,920
Nah. He's great.

526
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,000
[Mimicking "Mr. Wonderful"]
# Mr. Great. That's me #

527
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,000
Hey.

528
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,800
You drank too much.

529
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:02,320
I'm not drunk.

530
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:05,960
Why did you tell Annie
about Conrad's psychiatrist?

531
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:07,480
Why not?

532
00:32:07,560 --> 00:32:10,640
People don't hear
that thing easily.

533
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:14,160
For most people.
It's a status symbol.

534
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:16,640
Well. Your blurting it out...

535
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:18,640
was a violation of privacy.

536
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:20,160
Whose privacy?

537
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,040
The family's privacy!

538
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:25,040
I think it is
a very private matter.

539
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:35,080
I tell you my dreams?

540
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,560
I don't believe in dreams.

541
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:41,080
What kind of
a psychiatrist are you?

542
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:43,560
What's happening?

543
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,000
What's going on?

544
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:48,000
I just feel...

545
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:50,080
I feel so...

546
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,120
What?

547
00:32:53,200 --> 00:32:55,000
Jumpy. I don't know.

548
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,560
Look. Kiddo...

549
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:59,200
I lied.

550
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:02,240
I believe in dreams.

551
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:06,240
Sometimes I want to know
what's happening when you're awake.

552
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:08,640
Something's making you nervous.

553
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:11,160
Maybe I need a tranquilizer.

554
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,320
Tranquilizer?

555
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:14,720
What do you think?

556
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:18,240
You look like something
out of The Body Snatchers.

557
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:21,560
It's not my impression
that you need a tranquilizer.

558
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:25,120
What is this?

559
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,920
A clock.

560
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,440
You can tell the time.
But I can't.

561
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:33,600
So you know when
the hour's up?

562
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:34,960
Right.

563
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,640
50. 55 minutes?

564
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:49,160
Maybe I don't want
to swim anymore.

565
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:51,680
My timing is for shit.

566
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:55,200
Two guys better than me
swim the 50.

567
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:58,200
They're a bunch of boring jocks.

568
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:01,240
And him...
I can't stand him.

569
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:03,040
Thought about quitting?

570
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,120
You telling me to?

571
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,720
Nope.

572
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:07,920
It wouldn't look good.

573
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,360
How does it feel?

574
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:14,400
How does it feel?

575
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:16,880
Yes.
How does it feel?

576
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:22,160
It's the same damn thing
I did last year.

577
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:24,960
Are you the same
person now?

578
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:28,120
That's why you need
a tranquilizer?

579
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:29,240
You're a doctor.

580
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:32,600
I'm supposed to
feel better. Right?

581
00:34:32,640 --> 00:34:34,160
Not necessarily.

582
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:44,080
Is it getting any easier
with your friends?

583
00:34:44,160 --> 00:34:46,200
No. It's still hard.

584
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:48,200
Is anyplace easy?

585
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,440
The hospital was.

586
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,320
It was? Why?

587
00:34:57,480 --> 00:35:00,680
Because nobody
hid anything there.

588
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:04,400
Was there anyone there
you could talk to?

589
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:05,560
Uh-huh.

590
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:08,080
I mean, beside Dr. Crawford?

591
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,600
Uh-huh.

592
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,200
Whoa!

593
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,800
Hi.

594
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:20,800
Karen!

595
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:22,320
How are you?

596
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:23,480
Good.

597
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:24,960
Sit down. Please.

598
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,080
Thank you.

599
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:33,520
Wow.

600
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:58,360
When did you get back?

601
00:35:58,440 --> 00:36:00,360
The end of August.

602
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,360
Good.

603
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,360
It's great to see you.

604
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:05,400
Oh. You. Too.

605
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:08,880
Listen. I've got a meeting
over at the school.

606
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:10,400
Drama Club meeting.

607
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:12,880
We're doing
A Thousand Clowns.

608
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:14,400
You know it?

609
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:18,080
Anyway. We're going crazy
getting it together.

610
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:20,400
Don't let me hang you up.

611
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:24,120
No. I wanted to see you.

612
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:27,120
I didn't know what to expect.

613
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:30,120
You sounded funny on the phone.

614
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:33,120
It was just a gray day.

615
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:36,200
Everything's great.
I'm on the swim team.

616
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:37,880
Oh. You're swimming?

617
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,960
Terrific. Conrad.

618
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:41,560
That's really wonderful.

619
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:44,040
I could be benched all year.

620
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:46,440
You'll do great.

621
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:50,840
I'll bet your folks
are real proud of you.

622
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:51,840
Yeah.

623
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:54,200
What can I get you?

624
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:55,680
Are you hungry?

625
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:57,200
Just a coke.

626
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:59,640
Two cokes. Please.

627
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:01,480
Did we offend him?

628
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:02,680
Something I said?

629
00:37:04,120 --> 00:37:06,920
A low self-image day.

630
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:10,520
So. Uh...

631
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:11,880
- Are you...
- What did...

632
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:17,920
I can't believe
how beautiful you look.

633
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,320
You really look beautiful.

634
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,640
So do you.

635
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,360
Do you miss it?

636
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,600
Miss what?

637
00:37:25,640 --> 00:37:26,840
The hospital.

638
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:28,920
No.

639
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,680
Thank you.

640
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,480
You don't miss it?

641
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:33,680
No.

642
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:36,480
You don't miss Leo's corny jokes?

643
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:42,160
Are you seeing a doctor?

644
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:45,160
Yeah. I'm seeing one. Are you?

645
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:48,320
Uh. Dr. Crawford gave me a name.

646
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,800
I went for a while.

647
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,800
It didn't work.

648
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:56,320
He told me the things
I already knew.

649
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:57,840
Finally. I decided...

650
00:37:57,880 --> 00:38:00,960
the only one who
can help me is myself.

651
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:06,800
At least. That's what
my dad says.

652
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:09,480
If it's something
you want to do.

653
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:12,320
That's what you
should be doing.

654
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:16,160
I don't know
how long I'll keep it up.

655
00:38:19,040 --> 00:38:20,760
Your hair grew in.

656
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:25,160
Oh. That was such
a dumb thing to do.

657
00:38:25,240 --> 00:38:26,840
I like it.

658
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:28,360
You do?

659
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,840
Yeah.

660
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:34,360
I don't know.
I just...

661
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:36,360
I miss it sometimes.

662
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,880
The hospital.

663
00:38:37,920 --> 00:38:39,600
I really do.

664
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:44,440
Things have to change. You know?

665
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,720
But that's where we laughed.

666
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:49,120
But that was a hospital.

667
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:52,680
This is the real world.

668
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:54,600
I guess you're right.

669
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:04,360
I really have to go.

670
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,680
I'm sorry.

671
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:09,120
I have a meeting at the school.

672
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:11,640
We're doing A Thousand Clowns.

673
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:13,640
You told me.

674
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:17,280
Did I?

675
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,640
Yeah.

676
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,120
I better hurry.

677
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:23,640
Don't want to be late.

678
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:28,320
Thanks for seeing me.

679
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:31,640
Conrad?

680
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:35,240
Let's have a great Christmas.

681
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,680
Okay?

682
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:41,040
Let's have...

683
00:39:41,120 --> 00:39:43,600
a great year.

684
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:47,920
Let's have the best year
of our lives.

685
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:52,560
This could be
the best year ever.

686
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,080
Yeah.

687
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,320
Yeah.

688
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:57,520
Yeah.

689
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:01,920
Will you call me?

690
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:02,920
Yeah.

691
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:04,400
You mean it?

692
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:05,400
Yep.

693
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:09,400
You. Uh...

694
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:11,240
You look good. Conrad.

695
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,400
Yeah.

696
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:14,440
Bye.

697
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,760
Bye-bye.

698
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:19,720
Hey!

699
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:23,440
Would you cheer up?

700
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:04,720
It's cold.

701
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:09,200
You should put that on.

702
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:11,200
Do you want a sweater?

703
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,600
Do I need one?

704
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,720
What are you doing?

705
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:22,240
Nothing.

706
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:23,840
Thinking.

707
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:27,520
About what?

708
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:29,040
Not about anything.

709
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:36,040
Your hair is starting to grow out.

710
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:38,040
It's looking... looking better.

711
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:46,840
I was thinking
about the pigeon...

712
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:49,320
that hung around the garage.

713
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:54,160
How it used to get
on top of your car.

714
00:41:54,240 --> 00:41:55,720
Oh. Yeah.
I remember.

715
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:00,320
I remember
how scared I got...

716
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,320
That wsssshhhhh!
Flap. Flap. Flap...

717
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:05,320
Every time I started the car.

718
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:10,520
That was the closest
we came to having a pet.

719
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:15,000
Buck tried to talk you
into getting a dog.

720
00:42:15,080 --> 00:42:19,520
He said. "If it's the size
of a football?"

721
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:22,520
You know.
That animal next door...

722
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,600
that Pepper or Pippin...

723
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:26,440
Pippin. Pippin. Pippin.

724
00:42:26,520 --> 00:42:28,280
He's not friendly...

725
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:30,840
whatever Mr. McGreary says.

726
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:33,000
He wanted the retriever.

727
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:35,920
Each time that dog comes here.
I try to get him out.

728
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,120
Arf!

729
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:38,720
Arf! Arf!

730
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:45,560
Put that on
if you're staying out here.

731
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:26,720
Can I help?

732
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:28,240
With this?

733
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:30,400
No.

734
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:31,480
I will.

735
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:34,320
You can go to your room...

736
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:36,280
and clean the closet.

737
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:38,240
Mom.

738
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:40,320
Okay?

739
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:43,160
Because it's really a mess.

740
00:43:47,680 --> 00:43:49,560
[Telephone Rings]

741
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:50,120
[Telephone Rings]

742
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:55,440
[Ring]

743
00:43:58,040 --> 00:43:59,480
Hello.

744
00:43:59,560 --> 00:44:01,000
Oh. Hi.

745
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:03,000
I didn't get there.

746
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:05,000
How did it go?

747
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:07,480
No. I'm not doing anything.

748
00:44:07,560 --> 00:44:08,960
Just getting dinner ready.

749
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:10,720
Uh-huh.

750
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:12,240
Did she really?

751
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:19,760
Mary Ann Ramon started
just to scream. Right?

752
00:44:19,840 --> 00:44:22,760
We got so drunk.
We couldn't talk.

753
00:44:22,840 --> 00:44:26,040
It was the last day of school.

754
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:29,280
We walked out
of the building.

755
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,720
Oh, Bucky.

756
00:44:32,440 --> 00:44:34,520
No. Stop!

757
00:44:36,920 --> 00:44:39,240
What do you expect from her?

758
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:40,840
We just don't connect.

759
00:44:40,920 --> 00:44:41,800
Why not?

760
00:44:41,880 --> 00:44:43,280
We just don't.

761
00:44:53,880 --> 00:44:55,320
What are you thinking?

762
00:44:58,360 --> 00:45:01,280
That I jack off a lot.

763
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:03,320
So what else is new?

764
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:04,800
Does it help?

765
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:06,320
For a minute.

766
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:16,320
What now?

767
00:45:19,880 --> 00:45:21,840
John-Boy.

768
00:45:21,920 --> 00:45:23,320
Who?

769
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:25,320
John-Boy on
The Waltons.

770
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:27,640
Yeah.
What about him?

771
00:45:30,400 --> 00:45:33,360
After Buck died.
Dad came to my room.

772
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:36,520
He didn't
know what to say.

773
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:40,840
He put his
arm around me.

774
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:43,800
We just sat there.

775
00:45:43,840 --> 00:45:45,800
I remember watching his shoe.
And thinking...

776
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:52,280
His shoe was turned
over on its side.

777
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:56,680
I was thinking. He's so uptight!
It's gonna crack off.

778
00:45:59,680 --> 00:46:02,000
I knew I should've
felt something.

779
00:46:03,080 --> 00:46:05,800
I didn't know what to feel.

780
00:46:05,880 --> 00:46:10,320
On TV. They say stuff
like. "Oh. No!"

781
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:12,320
But I didn't say that...

782
00:46:12,400 --> 00:46:15,320
because I didn't feel sad...

783
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:16,840
so much as...

784
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:23,840
So much as what?

785
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:26,840
I kept thinking John-Boy
would've said something...

786
00:46:26,920 --> 00:46:28,680
about how he felt.

787
00:46:28,760 --> 00:46:31,080
What would he say?

788
00:46:33,920 --> 00:46:35,840
I don't know.

789
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:37,320
Come on.

790
00:46:42,600 --> 00:46:43,960
Come on.

791
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:46,240
Come on what?

792
00:46:46,320 --> 00:46:47,960
Don't hold back.

793
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:58,240
Well. At least
she's an improvement.

794
00:46:58,280 --> 00:47:00,240
That's what you get...

795
00:47:00,280 --> 00:47:03,240
when your partner
does the hiring.

796
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:04,720
That's my fault.

797
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:07,240
I can't tell anybody...

798
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:09,240
that they're not making it.

799
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,800
Wait a minute.

800
00:47:14,880 --> 00:47:17,320
That's not the problem.

801
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:18,800
Where are you?

802
00:47:18,880 --> 00:47:20,320
What?

803
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:23,320
I've been losing you these days.

804
00:47:25,400 --> 00:47:26,840
Oh. I'm sorry.

805
00:47:26,880 --> 00:47:28,840
That's okay.
That's okay.

806
00:47:28,880 --> 00:47:30,840
You off the track?

807
00:47:30,880 --> 00:47:32,320
Huh?

808
00:47:32,400 --> 00:47:35,320
Come on.
I've known you for 20 years.

809
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:36,840
Is something wrong?

810
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:38,320
How's Connie?

811
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:40,120
Connie's all right.

812
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:43,760
He is. He's okay.

813
00:47:44,840 --> 00:47:47,280
It's none of my business...

814
00:47:47,360 --> 00:47:49,800
but you worry too much.

815
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:54,280
You've been on the rack
about him long enough.

816
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:57,800
I'm not on the rack about him.

817
00:47:57,840 --> 00:48:00,800
In a year. He'll be gone.

818
00:48:00,840 --> 00:48:05,280
Off to Michigan
or wherever he wants to go.

819
00:48:05,360 --> 00:48:07,280
Maybe he'll tour Europe.

820
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:10,320
Who knows?

821
00:48:10,360 --> 00:48:12,800
I can't argue with "Who knows."

822
00:48:12,880 --> 00:48:15,800
I'm giving you the benefit
of my experience.

823
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:17,320
Thanks.

824
00:48:17,360 --> 00:48:20,800
Valerie isn't just
living away from home...

825
00:48:20,880 --> 00:48:22,320
she's gone.

826
00:48:22,400 --> 00:48:25,320
Got her own friends.
Her own life.

827
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:29,320
She breezes in
a few days on vacations.

828
00:48:29,400 --> 00:48:32,840
I don't know.
Maybe girls are different.

829
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:35,840
Or maybe she
was too aware...

830
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:39,840
of what was happening
between Nance and me.

831
00:48:39,880 --> 00:48:45,400
But they leave. And that
worrying's just wasted energy.

832
00:48:52,040 --> 00:48:54,400
[Young Conrad]
Give me back my sweater!

833
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:57,440
Hang on.

834
00:48:57,520 --> 00:48:58,560
[Bucky]
Dad, what's possession?

835
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:01,520
Give it to me!

836
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,840
It's already on me.

837
00:49:03,920 --> 00:49:05,360
Whose sweater is it?

838
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:07,280
It's my sweater!

839
00:49:07,360 --> 00:49:08,800
I'll give it back...

840
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:11,280
if you give me my skis.

841
00:49:11,360 --> 00:49:13,000
All right.

842
00:49:15,800 --> 00:49:18,360
Conrad! Conrad!

843
00:49:18,440 --> 00:49:19,480
What?

844
00:49:19,560 --> 00:49:21,440
[Man]
Watch your back.

845
00:49:21,520 --> 00:49:23,640
Cuts are vertical.

846
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:25,160
He really meant business.

847
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:27,080
Let's go.

848
00:49:27,160 --> 00:49:28,960
[Conductor]
Lake Forest is next.

849
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:30,600
Lake Forest.

850
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:02,880
[Laughing]

851
00:50:27,320 --> 00:50:28,880
What do you want?

852
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:32,360
I don't know
