01:05:16,080 --> 01:05:18,040
Nowhere.
The library mostly.

1136
01:05:18,080 --> 01:05:20,840
I didn't think it mattered.

1137
01:05:20,880 --> 01:05:23,320
That was meant for me.

1138
01:05:23,400 --> 01:05:26,640
It's important to hurt me. Right?

1139
01:05:26,720 --> 01:05:28,600
You have that backwards.

1140
01:05:28,680 --> 01:05:32,640
Do I embarrass you
in front of friends?

1141
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:36,720
"Poor Beth believes
every lie her son tells."

1142
01:05:36,800 --> 01:05:38,280
I didn't lie.

1143
01:05:38,360 --> 01:05:42,360
You did when
you came home at 6:30!

1144
01:05:42,440 --> 01:05:46,520
If the lying's starting again.
I can't stand it!

1145
01:05:46,600 --> 01:05:48,840
Then go to Europe!

1146
01:05:48,920 --> 01:05:54,280
She only gives a fuck because
someone else knew about it first!

1147
01:05:54,360 --> 01:05:57,680
She never came
to the hospital...

1148
01:05:57,760 --> 01:06:01,280
because she's busy going
to goddamn Spain and Portugal!

1149
01:06:01,360 --> 01:06:05,880
She doesn't care if I'm hung up
by the balls out there.

1150
01:06:05,960 --> 01:06:08,760
They may talk like this
at the hospital...

1151
01:06:08,800 --> 01:06:11,320
but we're not at the hospital.

1152
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:13,840
You never came to the hospital!

1153
01:06:13,920 --> 01:06:16,600
She had the flu
and couldn't come inside.

1154
01:06:16,680 --> 01:06:19,640
She would've visited Buck
in the hospital!

1155
01:06:19,720 --> 01:06:22,640
Buck never would've been
in the hospital!

1156
01:06:22,680 --> 01:06:24,360
That is enough!

1157
01:06:24,440 --> 01:06:27,160
I won't do it again.

1158
01:06:27,240 --> 01:06:29,840
What in hell has happened?

1159
01:06:29,920 --> 01:06:32,440
Somebody better go up there.

1160
01:06:32,520 --> 01:06:34,880
He walks all over us...

1161
01:06:34,920 --> 01:06:38,120
then you apologize to him.

1162
01:06:38,160 --> 01:06:39,920
You've been apologizing to him...

1163
01:06:39,960 --> 01:06:43,080
since he returned from the hospital!

1164
01:06:43,160 --> 01:06:46,600
I'm trying to
goddamn understand him!

1165
01:06:46,680 --> 01:06:48,320
Don't talk to me...

1166
01:06:48,400 --> 01:06:50,960
the way he talks to you.

1167
01:06:51,040 --> 01:06:53,480
Let's not fight. Okay?

1168
01:06:53,560 --> 01:06:55,120
No fighting. Okay?

1169
01:06:55,200 --> 01:06:57,080
Please.

1170
01:06:57,160 --> 01:06:58,800
Let's go upstairs.

1171
01:07:17,920 --> 01:07:20,320
I want to talk to you.

1172
01:07:20,400 --> 01:07:22,960
I didn't mean any of it.

1173
01:07:23,040 --> 01:07:25,200
Please don't be mad.

1174
01:07:25,280 --> 01:07:28,160
I'm trying to
understand what happened.

1175
01:07:28,240 --> 01:07:30,720
I don't know what happened.

1176
01:07:30,800 --> 01:07:32,720
I didn't mean it.

1177
01:07:32,800 --> 01:07:35,960
Tell her I'm sorry. Will you?

1178
01:07:36,040 --> 01:07:37,120
Why don't you?

1179
01:07:37,200 --> 01:07:38,960
God. I can't!

1180
01:07:39,040 --> 01:07:41,520
I can't talk to her!

1181
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:43,040
Why not?

1182
01:07:43,120 --> 01:07:45,080
It doesn't change anything.

1183
01:07:45,160 --> 01:07:49,720
It doesn't change
the way she looks at me.

1184
01:07:49,800 --> 01:07:53,800
She was hurt because
you quit the team.

1185
01:07:53,880 --> 01:07:56,360
I don't mean just now.

1186
01:07:56,440 --> 01:07:58,920
I don't mean just today.

1187
01:07:59,000 --> 01:08:01,000
Explain it to me.

1188
01:08:01,040 --> 01:08:04,040
I can't. You don't see things.

1189
01:08:04,120 --> 01:08:05,600
What things?

1190
01:08:05,680 --> 01:08:07,280
What things?

1191
01:08:07,360 --> 01:08:10,360
I want you to tell me.

1192
01:08:10,440 --> 01:08:13,520
Can't you see she hates me?

1193
01:08:13,600 --> 01:08:15,520
She doesn't hate you.

1194
01:08:15,560 --> 01:08:18,080
You're right.
She doesn't.

1195
01:08:18,160 --> 01:08:20,160
Please leave me alone.

1196
01:08:33,000 --> 01:08:36,440
Do you think Dr. Berger's helping you?

1197
01:08:36,520 --> 01:08:38,400
It's not his fault.

1198
01:08:44,520 --> 01:08:47,520
I'll be downstairs if you need me.

1199
01:08:51,960 --> 01:08:55,920
Tuesday everything was hunky-dory.

1200
01:08:56,000 --> 01:08:57,440
You're the doctor.

1201
01:09:00,440 --> 01:09:03,400
Don't take refuge
in one-liners. Okay?

1202
01:09:03,440 --> 01:09:05,400
Because that pisses me off.

1203
01:09:05,440 --> 01:09:07,880
Okay. Okay.

1204
01:09:07,960 --> 01:09:09,400
Everything was fine...

1205
01:09:09,480 --> 01:09:12,400
till you had the fight
with your mother?

1206
01:09:12,480 --> 01:09:13,880
I don't blame her.

1207
01:09:13,960 --> 01:09:16,400
She's got her reasons.
It's impossible...

1208
01:09:16,480 --> 01:09:18,400
after all the shit I've pulled.

1209
01:09:18,480 --> 01:09:20,400
What shit have you pulled?

1210
01:09:22,960 --> 01:09:25,320
I'm talking about proportion.

1211
01:09:25,400 --> 01:09:27,320
Now. What shit?

1212
01:09:30,400 --> 01:09:34,360
You can find one example.

1213
01:09:34,400 --> 01:09:36,360
Don't say you tried suicide.

1214
01:09:36,440 --> 01:09:38,360
What have you done lately?

1215
01:09:38,440 --> 01:09:42,040
I'll never be forgiven for that.

1216
01:09:42,120 --> 01:09:43,600
Never.

1217
01:09:43,680 --> 01:09:47,800
You can't get out
the blood in her towels...

1218
01:09:47,880 --> 01:09:49,880
and in her rug.

1219
01:09:49,960 --> 01:09:52,480
Everything
had to be pitched.

1220
01:09:52,560 --> 01:09:56,160
The bathroom tile
had to be regrouted.

1221
01:09:56,240 --> 01:09:57,960
She fired the maid...

1222
01:09:58,040 --> 01:10:00,880
because she couldn't dust right.

1223
01:10:00,960 --> 01:10:03,480
If you think I'll forgive...

1224
01:10:03,560 --> 01:10:05,040
she's gonna forgive me...

1225
01:10:13,040 --> 01:10:14,200
What?

1226
01:10:34,320 --> 01:10:38,080
I think I just figured
something out.

1227
01:10:38,160 --> 01:10:39,600
What?

1228
01:10:41,200 --> 01:10:43,640
Who it is who can't forgive who.

1229
01:10:48,920 --> 01:10:52,360
[Berger]
A real problem has a real solution.

1230
01:10:52,440 --> 01:10:54,440
[Conrad]
I've heard this before.

1231
01:10:54,480 --> 01:10:57,520
Doesn't make it any less true.

1232
01:10:57,600 --> 01:10:59,080
I'm so tired.

1233
01:10:59,160 --> 01:11:02,200
That's some secret
you've been keeping.

1234
01:11:02,280 --> 01:11:05,280
So what do I do now?

1235
01:11:06,920 --> 01:11:08,920
Recognize her limitations.

1236
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:12,520
Like she can't love me.

1237
01:11:12,600 --> 01:11:16,560
No. Like she can't
love you enough.

1238
01:11:16,640 --> 01:11:19,800
Don't blame her
for not loving you...

1239
01:11:19,840 --> 01:11:21,840
more than she's able.

1240
01:11:21,920 --> 01:11:23,920
She loves my father.

1241
01:11:24,000 --> 01:11:26,000
She loved my brother.

1242
01:11:26,080 --> 01:11:27,720
It's me.

1243
01:11:27,800 --> 01:11:30,880
We're back to
the rotten kid routine.

1244
01:11:30,960 --> 01:11:34,800
She can't love you
because you're unlovable.

1245
01:11:34,880 --> 01:11:37,960
How come your Dad loves you?

1246
01:11:38,040 --> 01:11:40,520
He feels responsible.

1247
01:11:40,560 --> 01:11:42,560
Besides. He loves everybody.

1248
01:11:42,640 --> 01:11:45,160
The guy's got no taste.

1249
01:11:45,240 --> 01:11:48,240
He loves you. But he's wrong.

1250
01:11:48,320 --> 01:11:49,800
Look...

1251
01:11:49,840 --> 01:11:52,840
maybe she can't express it...

1252
01:11:52,920 --> 01:11:54,880
the way you'd like.

1253
01:11:54,960 --> 01:11:58,240
Maybe she's afraid
to show her feelings.

1254
01:11:58,280 --> 01:12:00,520
What do you mean?

1255
01:12:00,600 --> 01:12:02,920
There's someone
besides your mother...

1256
01:12:03,000 --> 01:12:04,600
you've got to forgive.

1257
01:12:04,680 --> 01:12:06,440
You mean me?

1258
01:12:08,320 --> 01:12:10,840
For trying to off myself?

1259
01:12:12,960 --> 01:12:14,960
Don't stare.
What for?

1260
01:12:15,040 --> 01:12:19,000
Why don't you let yourself
off the hook?

1261
01:12:19,040 --> 01:12:22,080
What did I do?

1262
01:12:22,160 --> 01:12:23,760
What did I do?

1263
01:12:23,840 --> 01:12:25,280
We'll talk Thursday.

1264
01:12:25,360 --> 01:12:26,280
Come on!

1265
01:12:26,360 --> 01:12:28,080
Time's up.

1266
01:12:28,160 --> 01:12:30,600
What did I do?

1267
01:12:30,680 --> 01:12:32,080
You know the rules.

1268
01:12:32,120 --> 01:12:33,640
What rules?

1269
01:12:33,680 --> 01:12:35,400
Think about it.

1270
01:12:35,480 --> 01:12:37,040
Just think about it.

1271
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:41,480
Jesus!

1272
01:12:45,680 --> 01:12:48,240
Say. After going to a new high...

1273
01:12:48,320 --> 01:12:50,680
it falls to 1121/4...

1274
01:12:50,760 --> 01:12:53,760
and then rallies on good volume.

1275
01:12:53,800 --> 01:12:56,240
I order to buy 4.000.

1276
01:12:56,320 --> 01:13:00,600
If I get the 4.000 at 1133/4.
I know something's wrong.

1277
01:13:00,640 --> 01:13:04,600
But suppose I order
to buy the 4.000 shares...

1278
01:13:04,680 --> 01:13:07,520
and I plug in at 1133/4...

1279
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:11,480
I get 2.000 at 114.
500 at 1141/4...

1280
01:13:11,520 --> 01:13:14,400
and the rest on the way up.

1281
01:13:14,480 --> 01:13:16,480
Then I know I'm right.

1282
01:13:16,560 --> 01:13:19,440
I'm going to peel off here.

1283
01:13:19,520 --> 01:13:21,440
See you later.

1284
01:13:26,200 --> 01:13:28,800
[Voice Echoing]
Suppose the order to buy...

1285
01:13:28,880 --> 01:13:30,840
[Beth's Voice]
You let him walk all over us...

1286
01:13:30,880 --> 01:13:32,160
and you apologize.

1287
01:13:32,240 --> 01:13:33,880
[Man's Voice]
500 at 114...

1288
01:13:33,960 --> 01:13:35,920
[Conrad's Voice]
Dad, you don't see things.

1289
01:13:36,000 --> 01:13:37,800
[Beth]
You've been apologizing...

1290
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:41,160
since he returned from the hospital.

1291
01:13:41,240 --> 01:13:43,160
Tell her to stop it!

1292
01:13:43,240 --> 01:13:46,280
Buck never would've
been in the hospital!

1293
01:13:46,360 --> 01:13:47,720
She hates me!

1294
01:14:10,000 --> 01:14:11,720
I want to be clear.

1295
01:14:11,800 --> 01:14:13,600
That's good.

1296
01:14:15,480 --> 01:14:20,080
In the car.
I was thinking. "be clear."

1297
01:14:23,520 --> 01:14:25,960
I suppose that's what
psychiatry's about.

1298
01:14:26,000 --> 01:14:28,400
Being precise and clear.

1299
01:14:28,480 --> 01:14:30,440
And honest, of course.

1300
01:14:31,840 --> 01:14:35,800
I'm not a great believer
in psychiatry.

1301
01:14:35,880 --> 01:14:37,600
Okay.

1302
01:14:37,680 --> 01:14:41,320
What happens here
is between you and him...

1303
01:14:41,400 --> 01:14:43,400
and I respect that.

1304
01:14:43,480 --> 01:14:45,880
He's better.
I can see that.

1305
01:14:45,960 --> 01:14:48,760
I just don't believe in psychiatry...

1306
01:14:48,840 --> 01:14:52,080
as a panacea for everybody.

1307
01:14:52,160 --> 01:14:53,640
Neither do I.

1308
01:14:56,600 --> 01:15:01,160
I wish I knew what
I was doing here.

1309
01:15:01,240 --> 01:15:05,200
You said you could shed
some light on some things.

1310
01:15:05,280 --> 01:15:08,840
I meant in terms of Conrad.

1311
01:15:08,920 --> 01:15:11,400
I knew something was wrong...

1312
01:15:11,480 --> 01:15:13,960
even before he tried suicide.

1313
01:15:14,040 --> 01:15:16,040
But I thought that...

1314
01:15:17,120 --> 01:15:20,120
It's clear that he's very smart.

1315
01:15:20,200 --> 01:15:23,200
He's always been
an "A" student.

1316
01:15:23,280 --> 01:15:25,760
Naturally. I thought
intelligent people...

1317
01:15:25,840 --> 01:15:28,240
could work out their problems.

1318
01:15:28,320 --> 01:15:30,920
But you still feel responsible?

1319
01:15:30,960 --> 01:15:33,000
Yeah, sure I do.

1320
01:15:33,080 --> 01:15:35,120
It's hard not to.

1321
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:39,760
It was just luck that
I happened to be there...

1322
01:15:39,800 --> 01:15:41,800
when he tried it.

1323
01:15:41,840 --> 01:15:44,560
We both could've been away.

1324
01:15:44,640 --> 01:15:48,600
You think of yourself
as a lucky man?

1325
01:15:48,680 --> 01:15:50,200
No. No. No.

1326
01:15:50,280 --> 01:15:55,280
I used to think that
I was a lucky person...

1327
01:15:55,360 --> 01:15:57,040
before the accident.

1328
01:16:01,720 --> 01:16:04,720
I guess the whole of life...

1329
01:16:04,800 --> 01:16:07,280
is nothing but an accident...

1330
01:16:07,360 --> 01:16:09,200
what happens to you.

1331
01:16:09,280 --> 01:16:12,200
That sounds like
the philosophy of a drifter.

1332
01:16:12,280 --> 01:16:14,120
Yeah. Maybe.

1333
01:16:14,200 --> 01:16:16,520
Maybe I am drifting a little.

1334
01:16:16,600 --> 01:16:20,120
I can see the two of them...

1335
01:16:20,200 --> 01:16:22,200
drifting away from me...

1336
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:24,800
and I just stand watching.

1337
01:16:24,880 --> 01:16:29,040
What would you want
to do about that?

1338
01:16:29,080 --> 01:16:31,600
Something.
I don't know what.

1339
01:16:31,680 --> 01:16:35,120
I feel like
I'm sitting on a fence.

1340
01:16:35,200 --> 01:16:38,240
They're on opposite sides
of this fence?

1341
01:16:38,320 --> 01:16:41,040
Yeah... No.

1342
01:16:41,120 --> 01:16:42,320
I don't know.

1343
01:16:42,360 --> 01:16:46,960
I see her not being able
to forgive him.

1344
01:16:48,000 --> 01:16:49,560
For what?

1345
01:16:49,640 --> 01:16:51,560
I don't know exactly.

1346
01:16:51,640 --> 01:16:54,120
Being too much like her.

1347
01:16:54,200 --> 01:16:59,240
People always think that
she and Buck are... were alike.

1348
01:17:00,320 --> 01:17:03,320
But it's really she and Conrad.

1349
01:17:03,400 --> 01:17:05,880
They were the only two...

1350
01:17:05,960 --> 01:17:08,960
that didn't cry at the funeral.

1351
01:17:09,040 --> 01:17:13,080
It's not easy for me to admit this...

1352
01:17:13,160 --> 01:17:14,600
but. Um...

1353
01:17:14,680 --> 01:17:16,160
she didn't...

1354
01:17:20,160 --> 01:17:23,680
His mother doesn't
show him much affection.

1355
01:17:23,760 --> 01:17:27,400
I'm not trying
to put her down.

1356
01:17:27,480 --> 01:17:31,000
Did she give Buck
much affection?

1357
01:17:31,080 --> 01:17:33,520
God. Yes.
She loved Buck.

1358
01:17:33,600 --> 01:17:35,560
Bucky got so much.

1359
01:17:35,640 --> 01:17:39,160
What she felt for him was special.

1360
01:17:39,240 --> 01:17:41,760
He was her first-born.

1361
01:17:41,840 --> 01:17:43,600
And you?

1362
01:17:43,680 --> 01:17:45,160
I loved Buck.

1363
01:17:45,200 --> 01:17:47,360
I mean your wife's affection.

1364
01:17:47,440 --> 01:17:48,920
For me?

1365
01:17:49,000 --> 01:17:50,280
Yes.

1366
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:53,160
She's very...

1367
01:17:53,200 --> 01:17:57,320
No. There's no problem
with her for me.

1368
01:17:57,400 --> 01:18:01,080
We've been married
nearly 21 years.

1369
01:18:02,200 --> 01:18:03,640
Everybody loves Beth.

1370
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:07,120
For Conrad. It's been difficult.

1371
01:18:07,200 --> 01:18:10,000
He didn't talk about that?

1372
01:18:10,080 --> 01:18:13,080
We don't know what happens here.

1373
01:18:13,120 --> 01:18:15,120
It doesn't come up.

1374
01:18:19,560 --> 01:18:22,560
I guess that's what it is.

1375
01:18:22,600 --> 01:18:24,960
It's private here. Isn't it?

1376
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:26,440
Mm-hmm.
Very private.

1377
01:18:30,240 --> 01:18:34,160
I think I know why I came here.

1378
01:18:36,280 --> 01:18:39,600
I think I came here
to talk about myself.

1379
01:18:39,680 --> 01:18:42,440
Okay. Why don't we?

1380
01:18:48,920 --> 01:18:50,280
Hi.

1381
01:18:50,400 --> 01:18:54,360
[Car Buzzer Alarm]

1382
01:18:54,360 --> 01:18:55,320
Calvin?

1383
01:18:56,520 --> 01:18:58,360
[Buzzing Continues]

1384
01:18:58,440 --> 01:18:59,920
What's the matter?

1385
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:08,560
This will sound strange.

1386
01:19:10,120 --> 01:19:14,120
What I'm going to say
will sound strange.

1387
01:19:14,200 --> 01:19:15,680
What happened?

1388
01:19:15,720 --> 01:19:17,160
Come inside.

1389
01:19:18,520 --> 01:19:21,280
Could we talk about
Buck's funeral?

1390
01:19:21,320 --> 01:19:22,920
What?

1391
01:19:23,000 --> 01:19:27,000
It'll seem trivial.
But it's on my mind.

1392
01:19:27,080 --> 01:19:30,040
I'd like to talk about it.

1393
01:19:30,120 --> 01:19:34,040
When I was getting dressed
for Buck's funeral...

1394
01:19:34,120 --> 01:19:37,560
What could getting dressed
for Buck's funeral...

1395
01:19:37,640 --> 01:19:40,120
have to do with anything?

1396
01:19:40,200 --> 01:19:42,800
I was wearing a blue shirt.

1397
01:19:42,880 --> 01:19:47,440
You said. "Wear a white shirt
and other shoes."

1398
01:19:47,520 --> 01:19:52,600
It was nothing. But
it seemed to stay with me.

1399
01:19:52,680 --> 01:19:55,160
What difference did it make...

1400
01:19:55,240 --> 01:19:58,280
what I wore to Buck's funeral?

