Where are you?

1678
01:38:18,200 --> 01:38:19,760
I don't know.

1679
01:38:19,840 --> 01:38:21,280
All right.

1680
01:38:21,360 --> 01:38:23,320
Get to the office.

1681
01:38:23,360 --> 01:38:24,800
I'll meet you there.

1682
01:38:24,880 --> 01:38:26,120
Okay.

1683
01:38:30,320 --> 01:38:32,800
Good. You're here.

1684
01:38:32,880 --> 01:38:34,320
Something happened.

1685
01:38:34,400 --> 01:38:35,840
Just a minute.

1686
01:38:35,920 --> 01:38:38,400
Wait till we get inside.

1687
01:38:40,560 --> 01:38:41,480
There.

1688
01:38:43,080 --> 01:38:44,640
Shit.

1689
01:38:44,680 --> 01:38:48,400
You'd think they'd assume
there'd be emergencies.

1690
01:38:48,480 --> 01:38:50,320
Don't take it off.
Just sit down.

1691
01:38:55,080 --> 01:38:56,000
Something happened.

1692
01:38:56,080 --> 01:38:57,120
What?

1693
01:38:57,200 --> 01:38:58,600
It's...

1694
01:38:58,680 --> 01:39:00,080
It's what?

1695
01:39:00,160 --> 01:39:01,600
Oh. God!

1696
01:39:03,200 --> 01:39:04,760
I need something.

1697
01:39:04,840 --> 01:39:05,960
What?

1698
01:39:06,040 --> 01:39:07,520
It keeps coming.

1699
01:39:07,600 --> 01:39:09,480
I can't stop it!

1700
01:39:09,560 --> 01:39:11,160
Don't try.

1701
01:39:11,240 --> 01:39:13,760
Got to get off the hook.

1702
01:39:13,840 --> 01:39:15,440
For what?

1703
01:39:15,520 --> 01:39:17,600
What I did to him!

1704
01:39:17,680 --> 01:39:18,800
What?

1705
01:39:18,880 --> 01:39:21,320
It must be somebody's fault...

1706
01:39:21,400 --> 01:39:23,560
or there's no point!

1707
01:39:23,640 --> 01:39:25,640
What point? It happened!

1708
01:39:25,720 --> 01:39:28,760
Oh. No. I don't mean that.

1709
01:39:28,840 --> 01:39:30,320
It's just that...

1710
01:39:30,400 --> 01:39:32,920
Bucky. I didn't mean it.

1711
01:39:33,000 --> 01:39:36,000
Bucky, I didn't mean it.

1712
01:39:36,040 --> 01:39:37,880
Bucky!

1713
01:39:37,960 --> 01:39:38,960
It wasn't your fault.

1714
01:39:39,040 --> 01:39:41,360
You said. "Get the sail down!"

1715
01:39:41,440 --> 01:39:43,560
I couldn't! It jammed!

1716
01:39:43,640 --> 01:39:45,320
And then the halyard jammed!

1717
01:39:45,400 --> 01:39:47,320
Because the goddamned
halyard jammed!

1718
01:39:47,400 --> 01:39:50,320
Then you're sittin' here
screwing around!

1719
01:39:50,400 --> 01:39:52,120
Until it's too late!

1720
01:39:52,200 --> 01:39:55,360
And I'm supposed
to take care of it!

1721
01:39:55,440 --> 01:39:56,640
That wasn't fair.

1722
01:39:56,720 --> 01:39:59,640
No! And then
you say. "Hang on!"

1723
01:39:59,720 --> 01:40:00,800
"Hang on!"

1724
01:40:00,880 --> 01:40:02,520
Then you let go!

1725
01:40:02,560 --> 01:40:04,120
Why'd you let go?

1726
01:40:04,200 --> 01:40:05,440
I got tired!

1727
01:40:05,520 --> 01:40:08,160
Yeah? Well. Screw you. You jerk!

1728
01:40:20,640 --> 01:40:24,040
It hurts to be mad at him.

1729
01:40:24,120 --> 01:40:25,560
Yeah.

1730
01:40:27,840 --> 01:40:29,880
He just wasn't careful.

1731
01:40:29,920 --> 01:40:33,840
He didn't see how
a bad thing might happen.

1732
01:40:33,920 --> 01:40:37,680
Bad things happen even
when people are careful.

1733
01:40:37,760 --> 01:40:39,680
We should've come in...

1734
01:40:39,760 --> 01:40:42,360
when it started to look bad.

1735
01:40:42,400 --> 01:40:44,760
So you made a mistake.

1736
01:40:44,840 --> 01:40:47,120
Why did he let go?

1737
01:40:47,200 --> 01:40:48,680
Why?

1738
01:40:48,760 --> 01:40:51,800
Maybe you were stronger.

1739
01:40:51,880 --> 01:40:55,120
Did that ever occur to you?

1740
01:41:03,080 --> 01:41:06,080
How long will you
punish yourself?

1741
01:41:06,160 --> 01:41:07,280
When will you quit?

1742
01:41:07,360 --> 01:41:09,040
I'd like to.

1743
01:41:09,120 --> 01:41:10,440
Why don't you?

1744
01:41:10,520 --> 01:41:13,240
It's not that easy.

1745
01:41:19,840 --> 01:41:21,280
God...

1746
01:41:21,360 --> 01:41:23,320
I loved him.

1747
01:41:27,480 --> 01:41:29,440
I know.

1748
01:41:43,960 --> 01:41:47,160
What happened?
What started all this?

1749
01:41:47,240 --> 01:41:48,720
Karen.

1750
01:41:50,520 --> 01:41:52,800
She killed herself.

1751
01:41:52,880 --> 01:41:55,920
I just found out she's dead.

1752
01:41:56,000 --> 01:41:58,040
Jesus.

1753
01:41:58,120 --> 01:42:00,320
She was fine.

1754
01:42:00,400 --> 01:42:02,720
No. She wasn't.

1755
01:42:02,800 --> 01:42:06,280
She told me!
She said she was...

1756
01:42:06,360 --> 01:42:07,320
What?

1757
01:42:07,400 --> 01:42:10,160
She was busy and
feeling good and...

1758
01:42:10,240 --> 01:42:11,280
What?

1759
01:42:13,040 --> 01:42:14,240
What?

1760
01:42:14,320 --> 01:42:15,720
If I'd known...

1761
01:42:15,760 --> 01:42:17,280
I could've done something.

1762
01:42:17,360 --> 01:42:20,160
You're taking her on. Too?

1763
01:42:20,200 --> 01:42:21,160
No!

1764
01:42:21,200 --> 01:42:22,160
No?

1765
01:42:22,200 --> 01:42:23,680
No. I just...

1766
01:42:23,760 --> 01:42:24,680
What?

1767
01:42:24,760 --> 01:42:26,200
That isn't it.

1768
01:42:26,240 --> 01:42:29,360
I feel really bad about this.

1769
01:42:29,440 --> 01:42:32,760
Just let me feel bad about this!

1770
01:42:33,920 --> 01:42:35,240
Okay.

1771
01:42:37,520 --> 01:42:40,800
Listen. I feel
bad about it. Too.

1772
01:42:44,840 --> 01:42:47,360
Why do things
happen to people?

1773
01:42:47,440 --> 01:42:49,840
It isn't fair.

1774
01:42:49,920 --> 01:42:52,600
You're right.
It isn't fair.

1775
01:42:52,680 --> 01:42:55,080
You just do one wrong thing...

1776
01:42:55,160 --> 01:42:56,600
and...

1777
01:42:56,680 --> 01:42:59,280
Um-hmm.

1778
01:42:59,360 --> 01:43:03,200
And what was the one
wrong thing you did?

1779
01:43:10,160 --> 01:43:11,640
You know.

1780
01:43:24,640 --> 01:43:26,400
You know.

1781
01:43:29,400 --> 01:43:31,320
I hung on.

1782
01:43:31,400 --> 01:43:34,520
I stayed with the boat.

1783
01:43:34,600 --> 01:43:36,200
Exactly.

1784
01:43:41,920 --> 01:43:45,920
Now. You can live
with that. Can't you?

1785
01:43:52,080 --> 01:43:54,040
I'm scared!

1786
01:43:54,120 --> 01:43:56,320
I'm scared.

1787
01:43:56,360 --> 01:43:58,600
Feelings are scary.

1788
01:43:58,680 --> 01:44:00,760
And sometimes they're painful.

1789
01:44:00,840 --> 01:44:03,120
If you can't feel pain...

1790
01:44:03,200 --> 01:44:06,160
you won't feel
anything else.

1791
01:44:06,240 --> 01:44:08,840
You know what I'm saying?

1792
01:44:11,960 --> 01:44:13,520
I think so.

1793
01:44:16,480 --> 01:44:18,200
You're here. You're alive.

1794
01:44:18,280 --> 01:44:21,080
Don't say you don't feel that.

1795
01:44:21,120 --> 01:44:23,360
It doesn't feel good.

1796
01:44:23,440 --> 01:44:24,880
It is good.

1797
01:44:24,920 --> 01:44:26,400
Believe me.

1798
01:44:30,800 --> 01:44:32,680
How do you know?

1799
01:44:34,760 --> 01:44:36,960
Because I'm your friend.

1800
01:44:41,240 --> 01:44:44,680
I don't know
what I would've done...

1801
01:44:44,760 --> 01:44:47,200
if you hadn't been here.

1802
01:44:50,760 --> 01:44:53,480
You're really my friend?

1803
01:44:55,600 --> 01:44:58,400
I am. Count on it.

1804
01:45:51,160 --> 01:45:52,600
Hi.

1805
01:45:52,680 --> 01:45:54,080
I would've called...

1806
01:45:54,160 --> 01:45:57,080
but I didn't
want to wake anyone.

1807
01:45:57,160 --> 01:45:58,600
About the other night...

1808
01:45:58,680 --> 01:46:01,120
I liked being with you.

1809
01:46:01,160 --> 01:46:03,600
I didn't like myself.

1810
01:46:03,680 --> 01:46:05,600
Conrad. I was stupid.

1811
01:46:05,680 --> 01:46:08,600
That was dumb of me to laugh.

1812
01:46:08,680 --> 01:46:10,600
It was my fault.

1813
01:46:10,680 --> 01:46:12,720
I was embarrassed.

1814
01:46:12,800 --> 01:46:13,960
Really?

1815
01:46:14,000 --> 01:46:15,760
You were embarrassed?

1816
01:46:15,840 --> 01:46:18,080
When those boys came in...

1817
01:46:18,160 --> 01:46:20,640
it was awful and awkward.

1818
01:46:20,720 --> 01:46:23,000
When I'm embarrassed. I laugh.

1819
01:46:23,040 --> 01:46:26,360
They were just having
a good time.

1820
01:46:26,440 --> 01:46:30,400
I let them interfere
with what was happening.

1821
01:46:30,480 --> 01:46:31,920
It was dumb.

1822
01:46:32,000 --> 01:46:35,520
I've done lots of
dumb things lately.

1823
01:46:35,600 --> 01:46:40,320
I just didn't know if you were
being straight with me.

1824
01:46:43,440 --> 01:46:44,920
Yeah?

1825
01:46:45,000 --> 01:46:48,360
Anyway. I'd like
to try it again.

1826
01:46:48,400 --> 01:46:49,840
It worked okay...

1827
01:46:49,920 --> 01:46:52,040
except for the bowling.

1828
01:46:52,120 --> 01:46:53,600
Yes.

1829
01:46:53,640 --> 01:46:55,520
Yes?

1830
01:46:56,640 --> 01:46:58,680
Yes.

1831
01:46:59,760 --> 01:47:02,240
Are you going to school?

1832
01:47:02,320 --> 01:47:05,160
No. Not on Sunday.

1833
01:47:08,000 --> 01:47:10,000
Have you eaten?

1834
01:47:10,080 --> 01:47:12,080
No. I haven't.

1835
01:47:12,160 --> 01:47:14,600
Do you want some breakfast?

1836
01:47:16,560 --> 01:47:18,000
Okay.

1837
01:47:31,760 --> 01:47:33,040
Mom!

1838
01:47:34,920 --> 01:47:37,280
All right.
How about that?

1839
01:47:37,360 --> 01:47:38,800
Boy. Oh. Boy.

1840
01:47:38,880 --> 01:47:40,840
I do love that.

1841
01:47:40,920 --> 01:47:43,880
These holes sure do love you.

1842
01:47:43,960 --> 01:47:47,960
We should spend more time
playing golf together.

1843
01:47:48,040 --> 01:47:51,000
Maybe our next vacation...
strictly golf.

1844
01:47:51,080 --> 01:47:52,560
Pinehurst.
Myrtle Beach.

1845
01:47:52,600 --> 01:47:54,600
Pinehurst would be nice.

1846
01:47:54,640 --> 01:47:57,640
I think Connie would
like Pinehurst.

1847
01:47:57,720 --> 01:48:01,160
Is that deliberate
or just a reflex?

1848
01:48:01,240 --> 01:48:04,240
I assumed you meant him. Too.

1849
01:48:04,320 --> 01:48:07,280
I'm surprised you
haven't called him.

1850
01:48:07,360 --> 01:48:09,320
I'll call him tonight.

1851
01:48:09,400 --> 01:48:12,400
Can we have a little drink?

1852
01:48:12,480 --> 01:48:14,440
Drink. Yes. Little. No.

1853
01:48:14,520 --> 01:48:15,960
Let's finish this.

1854
01:48:16,040 --> 01:48:16,960
What?

1855
01:48:17,040 --> 01:48:18,520
What you started.

1856
01:48:18,560 --> 01:48:20,560
Me? There's no point.

1857
01:48:20,600 --> 01:48:22,080
He controls you.

1858
01:48:22,160 --> 01:48:24,120
He isn't the problem.

1859
01:48:24,160 --> 01:48:25,640
Isn't he?

1860
01:48:25,720 --> 01:48:29,120
No. Let's talk about
what's bothering you.

1861
01:48:29,200 --> 01:48:32,160
No. Let's discuss
what's bothering you.

1862
01:48:32,240 --> 01:48:36,240
How did I make you
so angry with me?

1863
01:48:36,320 --> 01:48:38,800
You blame me
for everything.

1864
01:48:38,840 --> 01:48:41,320
Can't you see
beyond yourself?

1865
01:48:41,400 --> 01:48:42,880
No. I can't!

1866
01:48:42,920 --> 01:48:45,920
Neither can you
or anybody else!

1867
01:48:46,000 --> 01:48:47,440
I'm just honest.

1868
01:48:47,520 --> 01:48:48,960
Stop being honest...

1869
01:48:49,040 --> 01:48:51,000
and start being generous!

1870
01:48:51,080 --> 01:48:52,520
Think about him!

1871
01:48:52,600 --> 01:48:55,560
What does he expect from me?

1872
01:48:55,640 --> 01:48:59,640
He wants a hug
when he passes exams?

1873
01:48:59,720 --> 01:49:02,720
I can't respond
when someone says...

1874
01:49:02,800 --> 01:49:05,760
"I did something
great. Love me."

1875
01:49:05,840 --> 01:49:09,800
He wants to know
you don't hate him.

1876
01:49:09,880 --> 01:49:12,400
Mothers don't hate their sons.

1877
01:49:12,480 --> 01:49:15,440
Is that what he told you?

1878
01:49:15,480 --> 01:49:19,480
You accept what he says
with no questions.

1879
01:49:19,560 --> 01:49:22,560
I'm trying to
keep this family...

1880
01:49:22,640 --> 01:49:25,600
What does everyone
want from me?

1881
01:49:25,680 --> 01:49:30,120
Listen. We all just
want you to be happy.

1882
01:49:30,160 --> 01:49:31,640
Happy?

1883
01:49:31,720 --> 01:49:32,680
Yes.

1884
01:49:32,760 --> 01:49:36,440
You tell me
the definition of happy.

1885
01:49:36,520 --> 01:49:39,800
First. Be sure your kids are safe...

1886
01:49:39,840 --> 01:49:43,360
that nobody's been hit by a car...

1887
01:49:43,440 --> 01:49:46,400
or drowned in your swimming pool!

1888
01:49:46,480 --> 01:49:50,000
Then tell me how to be happy!

1889
01:50:43,520 --> 01:50:46,000
I'm turning in.

1890
01:50:46,040 --> 01:50:47,520
Dinner was good.

1891
01:50:47,600 --> 01:50:49,040
Really good.

1892
01:50:49,120 --> 01:50:51,560
It's early. You tired?

1893
01:50:51,640 --> 01:50:53,880
It was a rough week.

1894
01:50:53,960 --> 01:50:57,680
Your grandmother
wasn't too tough on you?

1895
01:50:57,760 --> 01:50:59,720
No. She was fine.

1896
01:51:02,320 --> 01:51:04,840
I'm glad you're back.

1897
01:51:19,200 --> 01:51:20,640
Good night.

1898
01:52:39,440 --> 01:52:43,840
[Sobbing]

1899
01:52:50,560 --> 01:52:52,000
Calvin?

1900
01:53:03,960 --> 01:53:05,840
Why are you crying?

1901
01:53:12,720 --> 01:53:14,160
Can I. Uh...

1902
01:53:14,240 --> 01:53:16,720
Can I get you something?

1903
01:53:18,800 --> 01:53:20,280
I don't...

1904
01:53:20,360 --> 01:53:22,320
What did you say?

1905
01:53:26,480 --> 01:53:28,760
Calvin. What did you say?

1906
01:53:28,840 --> 01:53:30,360
[Sighing]

1907
01:53:33,320 --> 01:53:35,520
Tell me.

1908
01:53:42,160 --> 01:53:43,640
You are beautiful.

1909
01:53:47,240 --> 01:53:49,720
And you are unpredictable.

1910
01:53:51,840 --> 01:53:53,800
But you're so cautious.

1911
01:53:56,400 --> 01:53:57,840
You're determined. Beth...

1912
01:53:57,920 --> 01:54:00,040
but you know something?

1913
01:54:02,360 --> 01:54:03,960
You're not strong.

1914
01:54:06,040 --> 01:54:09,320
I don't know
if you're really giving.

1915
01:54:12,480 --> 01:54:14,000
Tell me something.

1916
01:54:14,080 --> 01:54:16,160
Do you love me?

1917
01:54:18,280 --> 01:54:20,720
Do you really love me?

1918
01:54:23,120 --> 01:54:26,920
I feel the way I've always
felt about you.

1919
01:54:39,560 --> 01:54:42,040
We would've been all right...

1920
01:54:42,080 --> 01:54:45,600
if there hadn't been any mess.

1921
01:54:47,200 --> 01:54:49,680
But you can't handle mess.

1922
01:54:51,280 --> 01:54:54,720
You need everything neat and easy.

1923
01:54:55,840 --> 01:54:57,320
I don't know.

1924
01:54:57,360 --> 01:54:59,840
Maybe you can't love anybody.

1925
01:54:59,920 --> 01:55:02,360
It was so much Buck.

1926
01:55:02,440 --> 01:55:07,440
It's as if you buried
all your love with him.

1927
01:55:07,520 --> 01:55:09,480
I don't understand that.

1928
01:55:11,080 --> 01:55:14,560
Maybe it wasn't even Buck.

1929
01:55:14,640 --> 01:55:17,040
Maybe it was just you.

1930
01:55:17,120 --> 01:55:22,760
Maybe, finally, it was
the best of you that you buried.

1931
01:55:25,320 --> 01:55:27,320
But whatever it was...

1932
01:55:30,920 --> 01:55:33,920
I don't know who you are.

1933
01:55:33,960 --> 01:55:38,480
I don't know what
we've been playing at.

1934
01:55:41,080 --> 01:55:43,200
So I was crying.

1935
01:55:47,720 --> 01:55:51,800
Because I don't know
if I love you anymore.

1936
01:55:54,840 --> 01:55:59,320
And I don't know
what I'll do without that.

1937
01:57:29,080 --> 01:57:30,040
[Door Slams]

1938
01:58:30,600 --> 01:58:31,680
Dad?

1939
01:58:34,920 --> 01:58:37,920
The yard looks smaller
without leaves.

1940
01:58:39,480 --> 01:58:40,960
Dad. What happened?

1941
01:58:43,080 --> 01:58:46,560
Your mother's
going away for a while.

1942
01:58:46,640 --> 01:58:47,800
Where?

1943
01:58:47,880 --> 01:58:49,080
Why?

1944
01:58:49,160 --> 01:58:50,640
Back to Houston.

1945
01:58:51,720 --> 01:58:53,160
I don't know.

1946
01:58:54,280 --> 01:58:55,720
Why? What...

1947
01:58:57,800 --> 01:58:59,280
I know why.

1948
01:58:59,360 --> 01:59:01,320
It's me. Isn't it?

1949
01:59:01,400 --> 01:59:02,360
No.

1950
01:59:02,400 --> 01:59:03,840
It's my fault.

1951
01:59:03,920 --> 01:59:06,200
Don't do that to yourself!

1952
01:59:06,240 --> 01:59:07,680
It's nobody's fault!

1953
01:59:07,760 --> 01:59:11,160
Things happen.
People don't always have answers.

1954
01:59:14,960 --> 01:59:18,760
I don't know why
I'm yelling at you.

1955
01:59:18,840 --> 01:59:21,920
You should do
that more often.

1956
01:59:22,000 --> 01:59:23,720
Haul my ass a little.

1957
01:59:23,800 --> 01:59:25,240
Get after me.

1958
01:59:27,560 --> 01:59:29,400
Like you did for him.

1959
01:59:29,560 --> 01:59:31,000
He needed it.

1960
01:59:31,080 --> 01:59:32,000
You didn't.

1961
01:59:32,080 --> 01:59:35,000
You were always
so hard on yourself.

1962
01:59:35,080 --> 01:59:37,400
I never had the heart.

1963
01:59:37,480 --> 01:59:40,000
Oh. Dad. Don't.

1964
01:59:40,080 --> 01:59:42,320
Well. It's the truth.

1965
01:59:44,080 --> 01:59:46,520
I never worried about you.

1966
01:59:46,600 --> 01:59:49,520
I just wasn't listening.

1967
01:59:50,680 --> 01:59:52,880
I wasn't sending
many signals then.

1968
01:59:52,960 --> 01:59:54,880
You couldn't do anything.

1969
01:59:54,920 --> 01:59:58,480
I should've got
a handle on it somehow.

1970
02:00:03,600 --> 02:00:07,560
I used to figure you had
a handle for everything.

1971
02:00:07,600 --> 02:00:09,840
You knew it all.

1972
02:00:09,920 --> 02:00:13,920
You always made us feel
everything would be all right.

1973
02:00:15,000 --> 02:00:17,960
I've thought about that
a lot lately.

1974
02:00:18,040 --> 02:00:20,480
I really admire you for it.

1975
02:00:20,560 --> 02:00:22,560
Don't admire people too much.

1976
02:00:22,640 --> 02:00:25,720
They'll disappoint you sometimes.

1977
02:00:26,880 --> 02:00:28,720
I'm not disappointed.

1978
02:00:31,920 --> 02:00:34,480
I love you.

1979
02:00:40,080 --> 02:00:41,520
I love you. Too.